It took Facebook another five years =E2=80=94 and the competitive threat of=
 TikTok =E2=80=94 but the company finally did make the leap to showing you =
content from across the entire service, not just that which was posted by y=
our network. The latter was an artificial limitation imposed by the company=
=E2=80=99s own self-conception of itself as a social network, when in reali=
ty it is a content network; true social networking =E2=80=94 where you talk=
 to people you actually know =E2=80=94 happens in group chats.

It=E2=80=99s unsurprising that this constraint in one part of the content v=
alue chain led to constraints in the recommendation algorithms; now, though=
, if you can access content from anywhere, well, it makes sense that recomm=
endation algorithms that pull from everywhere are more viable as well. To b=
e clear, Li noted that this is still an experiment, but I would be surprise=
d if this doesn=E2=80=99t work out in the long run, which will both lead to=
 better recommendations and lower costs =E2=80=94 which will help the reven=
ue to free cash flow ratio!

